Write as space-delimited, fixed-width file as required by NONMEM or a character-separated file

Source: R/nif_write.R
write_nif.Rd

All numeric fields are reduced to 4 significant places. For this, IEC 60559 is applied, i.e., rounding for a last digit of 5 is to the next even number. All fields are converted to character, and NA-values are converted to '.'.

Usage

write_nif(obj, filename = NULL, fields = NULL, sep = NULL)

Arguments

obj

The NIF object.

filename

The filename as string. If not filename is specified, the file is printed only.

fields

The fields to export. If NULL (default), all fields will be exported.

sep

The separating character, e.g. ',' or ';'. If NULL (default), the output has a space-separated, fixed-width format.

Value

Nothing.
